title: Barcelona vs Internazionale - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Semi Finals - 1st Leg
description: Barcelona and Internazionale have faced each other on 16 previous occasions in Europe, with the Spanish side winning exactly half of those. They are winless in the most recent two, however, which came in the group stages of the 2022-23 UEFA Champions League. This will be just the second time Barcelona and Internazionale have met in the knockout stages of the European Cup/UEFA Champions League, with both coming precisely at the semi-final stage. The previous one – played in 2009-10 – saw Jose Mourinho’s Inter eliminate the reigning champions 3-2 on aggregate.

title: Manchester United vs Athletic Club - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Sime Finals 2nd Leg
description: In all major European competitions, only one side has ever won the first leg of a two-legged knockout tie away from home by 3+ goals and failed to progress, with Maccabi Tel Aviv doing so against Olympiakos in the 2023-24 UEFA Conference League last 16. In the five previous matches between Manchester United and Athletic Club, there have been 22 goals, with the Red Devils scoring 12 and conceding 10. All five of those matches have seen at least three goals scored.

title: Bodø / Glimt vs Tottenham Hotspur - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Sime Finals 2nd Leg
description: In the history of the UEFA Europa League since its rebrand ahead of the 2009-10 season, there have been 92 instances of a side winning the first leg of a knockout match on home soil by a 2+ goal margin, of which only nine have failed to progress in the overall tie. All eight prior semi-finalists to achieve the feat have progressed to the final. Across their major European history, Bodø/Glimt have lost all four of their matches against English opposition, including their only one on home soil vs Arsenal in October 2022. Each of the other three defeats have seen the Norwegian side concede exactly three goals.

title: Internazionale vs Barcelona - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Semi Finals - 2nd Leg
description: This will be the 18th major European meeting between Internazionale and Barcelona, with only Bayern Munich vs Real Madrid, Juventus vs Real Madrid and Inter vs Real Madrid played more often in history. Each of the last two games between the teams have ended 3-3, in the UEFA Champions League in October 2022 and this season’s first leg. Barcelona have won just one of their six away UEFA Champions League matches against Internazionale, a 2-1 win in December 2019. Overall, Barca have managed just five wins in 24 away games in Italy, their lowest win ratio in any non-Spanish nation in the competition.

title: PSG vs Arsenal - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Semi Finals - 2nd Leg
description: PSG’s 1-0 win the first leg was their first ever victory in six attempts against Arsenal. Both of their home games against the Gunners have finished 1-1. Having been unbeaten in their first 13 away games against French sides in all competitions, Arsenal have now lost their last two visits against Rennes in 2019 and Lens in 2023.

title: PSG vs Internazionale - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Final
description: This is the first ever competitive meeting between Inter and Paris SG. It’s also the second European Cup/UEFA Champions League final between an Italian and a French side, after Marseille beat Milan 1-0 in 1993 – the only time a French side has ever won the trophy. That final was also held in Munich. This is Inter’s seventh appearance in the European Cup/UEFA Champions League final, winning the trophy three times. They did lose their last final match, going down 1-0 against Manchester City in 2023.

title: Tottenham vs Manchester Utd - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Final

title: Main Race - F1 Belgian Grand Prix - 2025
description: The crown jewel of F1 circuits hosts Round 13 of the 2025 season. Spa-Francorchamps offers 7 km of high-speed thrills, elevation changes, and strategic unpredictability—making this one of the most anticipated races of the year.

title: Qualifying - Budapest Round - Porsche SuperCup - 2025
description: With identical 911 GT3 Cup cars, Porsche SuperCup qualifying is a test of driver skill and bravery. Nailing a clean lap while managing track limits around the Hungarorings unforgiving curves is the ultimate goal.

title: Race - Budapest Round - Porsche SuperCup - 2025
description: A fierce one-make race that delivers non-stop action from lights out to the chequered flag. Door-to-door battles, late braking, and slipstream duels define this showcase of elite GT racing on F1’s support bill.

title: Qualifying - FIA Formula 3 Championship - Budapest Round -2025
description: Formula 3’s stars of tomorrow go head-to-head in a tight qualifying session where track evolution and traffic can make or break a lap. A clear run and clever use of slipstream are vital to securing a strong starting position.

title: Sprint Race - FIA Formula 3 Championship - Budapest Round -2025
description: This short-distance, reverse-grid race rewards fast reactions and bold passing. The format creates close pack racing where quick decision-making, slipstreaming, and corner defence play central roles.

title: Feature Race - FIA Formula 3 Championship - Budapest Round -2025
description: The main race for the F3 weekend offers full championship points and usually features the cleanest racing lines. Starting positions are based on qualifying, and with tyre degradation at play, drivers must be aggressive yet controlled to emerge victorious.

title: Qualifying - FIA Formula 2 Championship -Budapest Round -2025
description: Formula 2 qualifying sets the stage for a pivotal race weekend. Drivers go all out on soft tyres to earn the best possible grid slot for the Feature Race. Budapest’s twisty circuit punishes overdriving, so consistency and accuracy are key.

title: Sprint Race - FIA Formula 2 Championship -Budapest Round -2025
description: With a reversed top-10 grid and fewer laps, the Sprint Race features quick bursts of action and opportunistic overtaking. There are no scheduled pit stops, so tyre conservation and launch technique at the start are crucial to making up positions.

title: Feature Race - FIA Formula 2 Championship -Budapest Round -2025
description: The crown jewel of the F2 weekend, the Feature Race includes mandatory pit stops and a full strategy game. Drivers need strong tyre management and composure to make overtakes count. With more points on offer, this race is essential in the title fight.

title: Main Race Qualifying - FIA Formula 1 World Championship - Hungarian GP - 2025
description: High stakes and razor-thin margins define this F1 qualifying session. Drivers must deliver perfect laps under pressure, navigating the narrow Hungaroring layout where overtaking is rare. Pole position is vital, and one mistake can mean starting far back on the grid.

title: Main Race - FIA Formula 1 World Championship - Hungarian GP - 2025
description: The Grand Prix unfolds over 70 demanding laps, where strategy, precision, and discipline rule. Track position plays a major role, so undercuts and tyre tactics become decisive. With little margin for error, the Hungarian GP often rewards intelligent racecraft over sheer speed.
